<title type="html"><![CDATA[12/5 (Thu.) What's Your Biggest Regret? / Tidying Up with Marie Kondo &amp; Hoarders (Host: Sherry Yang)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=340&amp;p=356#p356"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-weight: bold">Session I: What's Your Biggest Regret? (Nobody Wants to Admit the Worst One of All)</span><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R45HcYA8uRA" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R45HcYA8uRA</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion questions:</span><br />1.Do you regret something you have ever done or never done? What are they?<br /><br />2.Why do you think people have regrets in the first place? Explain.<br /><br />3.Should we live with no regrets completely or learn how to somehow live with our regrets?<br /><br />4.What’s the best way to make regrets hurt less? Or how do you make regrets go away?<br /><br />5.What’s the one thing you would change in your life if you could travel back in time?<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session II: Tidying Up with Marie Kondo &amp; Hoarders </span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Tidying Up with Marie Kondo Official trailer (HD)/Netflix </span><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WvyeapVBLWY" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WvyeapVBLWY</a><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">What Turns People into Hoarders?</span><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yaxHU7LHJt0" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yaxHU7LHJt0</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion questions:</span><br />1.How tidy are you? Do you agree with Marie Kondo’s method of “tidying up”? <br /><br />2.Do you have a hard time getting rid of stuff? Please share your experience.<br /><br />3.What causes someone to be a hoarder?<br /><br />4.How do you deal with a hoarder?<br /><br />5.What is hoarding disorder? Is hoarding a mental health problem?<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Agenda</span><br />7:00 p.m. --7:20 p.m. Free talk<br />7:20 p.m. --7:50 p.m. First topic discussion<br />7:50 p.m. --8:15 p.m. Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited)<br />8:15p.m.-- 8:45 p.m. Second topic discussion<br />8:45 p.m.-- 9:00 p.m. Presentation (Participants that haven't presented yet are invited)<br />speaker time: 2 minutes for each speaker<br />host time: 3 minutes<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">The meeting place of Thursday:</span><br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第三區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=827">Jason Tang</a> — Thu Nov 28, 2019 9:58 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
